'''Carlos Andrés Gómez Hinestroza''' (born 12 September 2002) is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] or [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|andres-gomez/803617}}</ref>

==Club career==
Gómez's professional debut for Millonarios shirt came on 14 November 2021 in a game against [[Alianza Petrolera]]. His first Millonarios goal was on 1 May 2022 against [[Patriotas Boyacá]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infobae.com/america/colombia/2023/01/05/la-fortuna-que-ganaria-millonarios-con-la-venta-de-carlos-andres-gomez-a-la-major-league-soccer|title=The fortune that Millionaires would earn with the sale of Carlos Andrés Gómez to Major League Soccer|website=Infobae.com|date=5 January 2023 }}</ref> In September 2022 Gomez signed a new contract with the club lasting into 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futbolred.com/futbol-colombiano/liga-betplay/carlos-andres-gomez-de-millonarios-y-la-primera-oferta-de-club-brasileno-173003|title= Carlos Gómez, el interés es serio: primera oferta de equipo de Brasil|website=Futbolred.com|date= 21 December 2022}}</ref> His form helped his club qualify for the [[Copa Libertadores]] by winning the [[2022 Copa Colombia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.semana.com/deportes/articulo/andres-gomez-una-de-las-joyas-de-millonarios-que-podria-jugar-en-el-exterior/202259/|title= Andrés Gómez, one of the Millionaires jewels that could play abroad|website=Semana.com|date= 20 December 2022}}</ref> Goméz was thought to be moving to Brazil in December 2022 to [[Red Bull Bragantino]] but the transfer fell through repeatedly due to disagreements over the financial structure of the deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futbolred.com/futbol-colombiano/liga-betplay/carlos-andres-gomez-avanza-con-dialogos-con-el-real-salt-lake-de-la-mls-173755|title= Carlos Gómez seducido por la MLS: un equipo está al margen y avanza|website=Futbolred.com|date= 5 January 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eldeportivo.com.co/futbol-colombiano/millonarios/real-salt-lake-avanzo-en-el-fichaje-de-carlos-andres-gomez/|title=Real Salt Lake advanced in the signing of Carlos Andrés Gómez|website=Eldeportivo.com|date=5 January 2023 }}</ref>

On 10 January 2023, Gómez signed with [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Real Salt Lake]] on a five-year deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rsl.com/news/real-salt-lake-acquire-colombian-winger-carlos-andres-gomez-from-millonarios-fc|title=Real Salt Lake Acquire Colombian Winger Carlos Andrés Gómez From Millonarios FC &#124; Real Salt Lake|website=rsl}}</ref>

On 17 August 2024, Gómez joined [[Ligue 1]] side [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Real Salt Lake Attacker Andrés Gómez Transferred to French Ligue 1 Side Stade Rennais |url=https://www.rsl.com/news/real-salt-lake-attacker-andres-gomez-transferred-to-french-ligue-1-side-stade-rennais |publisher=[[Real Salt Lake]] |access-date=23 August 2024 |date=17 August 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Andrés Gómez Joins Stade Rennais F.C. |url=https://www.staderennais.com/en/news/carlos-andres-gomez-est-rouge-et-noir |publisher=Stade Rennais |access-date=23 August 2024 |date=17 August 2024 }}</ref>

On 21 January 2026, Gómez signed a contract with [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]] until January 2031, after playing for the club on loan previously.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CR Vasco da Gama|url=https://vasco.com.br/vasco/vasco-da-gama-acerta-a-compra-do-atacante-andres-gomez/|title=Vasco da Gama acerta a compra do atacante Andrés Gómez|trans-title=Vasco da Gama finalizes the purchase of striker Andrés Gómez.|date=21 January 2026|access-date=21 January 2026|language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
He made his international debut for [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] on 10 December 2023, against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]] in Fort Lauderdale.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/12/11/world/friendlies/colombia/venezuela/4271483/ |website=Soccerway|date=10 December 2023|title=COLOMBIA VS VENEZUELA 1-0|accessdate=18 December 2023}}</ref> He scored his first international goal the following week on his second appearance, in a 3–2 international friendly win against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] in Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.latimes.com/sports/soccer/story/2023-12-16/mexico-loses-colombia-friendly-coliseum |newspaper=LA Times|accessdate=18 December 2023|title= Mexico shows its inexperience as Colombia rallies to victory at Coliseum |date=17 December 2023}}</ref>

